Incident.Summary: A vehicle stop for the driver not having been restrained by a seat belt led to a probable cause search of the vehicle, based on the odor of Marijuana, which revealed the driver was in possession of Marijuana and Crack/Cocaine with the intent to distribute.

IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText: In-car body camera operational, T-36. TRAINING CERTIFICATIONS: Associates Degree in Police Science through Frederick Community College (2021) A.R.I.D.E. Trained Through Calvert County Sheriffs Office- 03/29/2022 - 03/30/2022 (NCJTC) NATIONAL CRIMINAL JUSTICE TRAINING CENTER OF FOX VALLEY TECHNICAL COLLEGE - Drug Identification - Antidepressants Inhalants Certification (04/06/2022) (NCJTC) NATIONAL CRIMINAL JUSTICE TRAINING CENTER OF FOX VALLEY TECHNICAL COLLEGE - Drug Identification - Stimulants (4/7/2022) FMCSA DIAP 24 Hour - Commercial Interdiction Training (04/19/22-04/21/2022) Basic Criminal Investigator School Maryland State Police (05/16/22-05/20/22) Street Cop Training - Interdiction Mastermind (05/24/2022) Street Cop Training - Deceptive Behaviors Hidden Compartments Commercial Motor Vehicle Weights Measures Certified Level III Certified Commercial Vehicle Enforcement Officer margin-left:8px">Maryland State Police Complete Traffic Stop Training SCENE PROCESSING: The CDS was seized and documented on a MSP Form 67, Chain of Custody, and Property Record P-344499. The CDS was transported to the Maryland State Police Leonardtown Barrack, where it was packaged and stored pursuant to agency policy. The suspect vehicle was seized and a MSP Form 91D Vehicle Inventory Checklist/Worksheet was completed. NARRATIVE: On June 8, 2023 at approximately 1422 hours, I, Trooper Black #7094, was on-duty, on patrol, in uniform, operating marked patrol vehicle T-36, in the area of MD Route 5 at Mount Wolf Road, Charlotte Hall, St. Marys County, Maryland 20622. I observed a silver, Lexus LS430, passenger car pass my vehicle. I observed the driver was not restrained by a seat belt. I allowed the vehicle to pass my location, pulled behind the vehicle, activated my emergency equipment, and initiated a traffic stop.The vehicle stopped on Mohawk Drive at MD RT 5. I made contact with the driver of the vehicle, who was the sole occupant, via the passenger side front window. I identified the driver by his Maryland drivers license as Devonte Ali Thomas (B/M, DOB: 03/01/1996). Upon contact, I detected the strong odor of burnt Marijuana emitting from inside the vehicle. I requested Trooper Louderback #6738 respond to my location. I requested Thomas to exit his vehicle. As Thomas exited his vehicle, he reached in his sweatshirt pocket and handed me a glass jar, containing Marijuana. Thomas began pacing back and forth behind his vehicle. I instructed Thomas to sit on the curb, and he complied. Thomas suddenly stood up, and I gave him verbal commands to sit down. Thomas began backing away. I attempted to grab Thomas, but he began running away. I gave Thomas verbal commands to lay on the ground, to which he did not comply.Thomas did, however, stop running, turn around, and began walking back to my location then proceeded to turn back around and continued running away again. Thomas continued to run on Mohawk Drive as Trooper Louderback #6738, arrived on scene and caught up to Thomas. Thomas ran a short distance from Trooper Louderbacks vehicle, as Trooper Louderback gave chase on foot. Trooper Louderback caught up to Thomas and detained him. Thomas stated he wanted to call his mother. Thomas left his vehicles keys in the ignition. I obtained the keys, secured Thomass vehicle, and drove to their location. Thomas was placed under arrest and secured in my vehicle, in front of 37726 Mowhawk Drive. Both units responded back to Thomass secured vehicle. A probable cause search of the vehicle yielded the following results: PROPERTY RECORD: P-344499 ITEM A: One (1), ziplock bag, containing one, plastic bag, containing suspected Crack/Cocaine; Weight: 24.4 Grams Location: Underneath the drivers seat. CURRENCY: ITEM A: One (1), evidence envelope, containing $1215 U.S. Currency; Denominations: 100s: 4 50s: 4 20s: 26 10s: 8 5s: 3 margin-bottom:11px">Location: Drivers seat (packaged in two separate stacks; one rubber banded) Through my training, knowledge, experience, and previous CDS arrests/convictions, I was able to identify the above listed CDS and CDS paraphernalia. I also know that Crack/Cocaine is a known Controlled Dangerous Substance; Schedule II. I also know that Marijuana is a known Controlled Dangerous Substance; Schedule I. I recognized that the amount of Crack/Cocaine and Marijuana that was seized, coupled with the U.S. currency in multiple denominations, the manner in which the CDS was packaged, the presence of the digital scale, and the additional baggies, is indicative of the intent to distribute and not solely for personal use. Thomas was read his Miranda Rights, via my agency issued Advice of Miranda Rights card. Thomas invoked his right to remain silent, and he was not asked any further questions. The CDS and U.S. currency were seized and transported to the Maryland State Police Leonardtown Barrack by me, where it was packaged and stored pursuant to agency policy. Thomass vehicle was seized and a MSP Form 91D Vehicle Inventory Checklist/Worksheet was completed. The vehicle was transported to the Maryland State Police Leonardtown Barrack, where it was processed and stored pursuant to agency policy. Trooper Louderback escorted the suspect vehicle as it was transported to the barrack. Thomas was transported to the St. Marys County Detention Center, where he was charged criminally, issued the appropriate citations, and released to detention center staff. A copy of Thomas FAR and MSP Form 253 were forwarded to Asset Forfeiture. A wage check will be requested, and a supplement will be completed upon receipt. All events occurred in St. Marys County, Maryland. I request this case remain open.

IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText: Mode of Operation: Probable cause exists to believe that the suspect vehicle was used to facilitate drug trafficking. Suspect(s): THOMAS, Devonte Ali (B/M, DOB: 03/01/1996) 12455 Shiloh Church Road, Newburg, MD 20644 Vehicle: 2003 Lexus LS430, Vin: JTHBN30F330113119, Registration: VA/TTC8386 Mileage: 266,617 NADA Value: $7,150 Narrative: On 6/8/2023 I, Senior Trooper Logsdon, received paperwork from the Leonardtown Barrack in reference to a vehicle seizure. Probable cause exists to believe that the suspect vehicle was used to facilitate drug trafficking. Refer to IR 23-MSP-020541 for further. The 2003 Lexus LS430 is solely registered to THOMAS. On 06/08/2023 the Maryland State Police receipt for Seized Property (Form 253) was authorized and presented to THOMAS, which he signed. On 06/15/2023 a Criminal History check was conducted on Warren, which revealed the following: 4/7/2021 - CDS: POSSESS-NOT MARIJUANA - STET 3/11/2011 - CON-CDS DISTRIBUTE - COCAINE - Guilty 3/11/2011 - CDS: Possess-Not Marijuana - Nolle Pros 3/11/2011 - CDS POSS W/INT TO DIST - Nolle Pros 3/11/2011 - CDS: Possess-Not Marijuana - Nolle Pros On 06/15/2023, I emailed Mark Bowen, assistant Attorney General of the Maryland State Police Legal Counsel Unit. Mark Bowen concurred with moving forward with the vehicle forfeiture. On 07/05/2023 I requested a certified title from Virginia Department of Motor Vehicles. I have reviewed, documented, recorded, and forwarded all necessary reports to the Legal Counsel Unit for the initiation of forfeiture proceedings on the vehicle. A supplemental report will be written advising the disposition of the vehicle upon adjudication of the case. This case is closed with nothing further to report at this time. M/Tpr Logsdon 4 hours.

NARRATIVE: In accordance with Settlement Agreement, between Devonte Thomas and the State of Maryland, through respective counsel, the State of Maryland is to receive $1,100.00 for the release of the vehicle to Mr. Thomas. On September 14, 2023, Assistant Attorney General Mark H. Bowen, of the Legal Counsel Section, prepared a memorandum authorizing the release of the 2003 Lexus LS430 to Mr. Thomas. On September 26, 2023, the 2003 Lexus LS430 was released in Mr. Thomas custody. I subsequently completed the Abandoned/Impound Vehicle Report documenting the release of the vehicle to Mr. Thomas. On October 24, 2023, in accordance with this agreement, the SunTrust check #29823, drawn from Iolta Vallario and Collins Escrow account, payable to the State of Maryland, in the amount of $1,100.00, was forwarded to the Finance Division for deposit into the General Fund. Copies of all related documents are incorporated as part of this file. This case is closed with nothing further to report. Case closed. M/Tpr. Logsdon - 1 hr
